n><hr size=1> It's a long string I know. But I'm sure you'll enjoy it. I did this one last year...<br>
<br>
Ode To The Mind<br>
<br>
Spring has come on deep wings of solitude,<br>
   Abysmal clouds cover gray fleeting sky,<br>
       Sounds of the wind cease to be of multitude.<br>
    Heavy frigid air passing up on high,<br>
      Minds Ionic column on pedestal<br>
    In frozen temple, resting immortal. <br>
         Outside green grass doth ripen, ever chilled,<br>
    Lone trees rest, branches in silent stillness;<br>
Brown earth although still fallow has been tilled,<br>
December’s ebbed and summer still far light.<br>
<br>
Wine retained in ample harvest last year<br>
    Goes to warm lonely heart and every thought,<br>
       Gleaming Chariots drive upon thy lot:<br>
    Seeking ever higher and never stop.<br>
       Relentless pen drives on to epitome,<br>
           For e’er the soul seeks blind transcendency;<br>
           With pitched dark cloud and mists a-brooding-by,<br>
   Upon fading, secluded, Avalon.<br>
Silent, unbound spirit, seeks cognizance,<br>
And true pictorial face left anon.<br>
<br>
Single light lies a beacon of night:<br>
    Through embalming fog, luminous, still shine,<br>
        Touch lost traveling vision of my sight<br>
          In intellects dark absence wither, pine;<br>
       Conform not to landscapes dreary shadow<br>
   Seek not coldly subtle untamed sorrow.<br>
             Do not submit so eas’ly to the tomb,<br>
    Breathe steadily on, till life’s spacious last breath;<br>
As Times great specter travels faintly by<br>
Look not down, but up, up into the sky.<br>
<br>
Fly Thought! On high, to World’s sister orb;<br>
     On Pegasus not or simple line,<br>
          But on infinite wings herald Poesy:<br>
     Clustered ‘round by stars all faery and fine,<br>
        Listen not to the world that often binds.<br>
     Tread long on silvery dust and leave thine print,<br>
           Travel on slow tide ‘round from dark to light.<br>
     Solace forge precious gem of minds mint;<br>
Sail on Skies’ occult impassioned ardor<br>
To Deep Universes’ boundless harbor.  <br>
<br>
When midnights’ muse has come to toll the bell,<br>
     Forever Mindful-Ocean will she quell;<br>
          Days of ever darkened sight will eye see:<br>
     Fall off thy branch and become root of tree.<br>
          Wisdom of the soul doth about entrance<br>
    All who pass by its static stone of age:<br>
            Captured by calm presiding elegance;<br>
    Tribute to once noble, Earthly, sage.<br>
Ride on Legends ship to heaven’s escape,<br>
Life’s last, final stage is now consummate.<br>
<br>
All those who seek the temple, extol its grain:<br>
       Through peril, strife, pain, only will thy gain;<br>
          Entrance upon the Stoic’s memory, <br>
       Find sweet maidens blissful epiphany.<br>
              Yet half, still entranced by insightful death:<br>
      Approach column of ever-timeless rhyme<br>
          And praise the lark on which it has e’er sung;<br>
      Hear the bells of Heaven’s festival chime,<br>
Repeat candid verse upon common tongue,<br>
And mind, although in death will be in birth. <br>
<br>
-Falcon<br>
